(1)
69th Place (right, beyond body of water), south from Calamus Ave., showing the Sedgewick House (tower thereon), said to have been built in the 1870'e. It was still standing in 1934.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, viewed southeastward across fields from point just socth of alamus Ave. and west of 69th Place, showing the undewweloped
condition of 69th Place (along line of fence).
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
